article.headline: Vanderbilt 90, Wofford 59
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Matt Freije scored 21 of his 24 points in the first half and Vanderbilt matched its best start in the last 30 years with a 90-59 victory over Wofford on Saturday night. Vanderbilt is now 8-0 for just the second time since the 1973-74 team started 10-0. Vanderbilt shot 56 percent for the game, including 61 percent in the second half. The Commodores hit 10 of their first 12 shots after halftime. Sam Daniels led Wofford (3-6) with 14 points. Justin Stephens had 13 points and Adrien Borders had 12. Dawid Przybyszewski scored 14 points and Jason Holwerda had 10 points and seven assists for Vanderbilt. Scott Hundley had a game-high nine rebounds to go along with eight points off the bench. Vanderbilt broke the game open with a 17-2 run early in the second half that gave the Commodores a 57-29 lead. Holwerda had a breakaway dunk and layup during the run and Corey Smith had a reverse layup. Vanderbilt's largest lead was 89-50 with three minutes to play. Julian Terrell, who started the first seven games at center for Vanderbilt and averaged 9.3 points, missed the game with a back injury. Vanderbilt's average margin of victories during its 8-0 start is 21.4 points.
